The area of the right triangle is $\frac{1}{2} x^2,$ and the area of the pentagon is $x^2 + \frac{1}{2} x^2 = \frac{3}{2} x^2.$  Therefore, the ratio of the area of the right triangle to the area of the pentagon is
\[\frac{1/2 \cdot x^2}{3/2 \cdot x^2} = \frac{1}{3},\]which is $\boxed{33\frac{1}{3}}$ percent.

