The height of the right triangle is $s,$ so the height of the pentagon is $2s.$  The area of the pentagon is then
\[\frac{1}{2} s^2 + \frac{1}{2} (2s) s = \frac{3}{2} s^2.\]Therefore, the ratio of the area of the right triangle to the area of the pentagon is
\[\frac{1/2 s^2}{3/2 s^2} = \frac{1}{3} = \boxed{33.33\%}.\]

